# {{SYSTEM_NAME}} Design System — UI Gate Hook

Automatic, deterministic gate that runs whenever the agent finishes editing UI
source, so design-system drift can never reach "done" unnoticed.

## Trigger

Fires on **UI-edit completion** — after the agent has finished creating or
modifying any UI source file:

- `.tsx`, `.ts`, `.jsx`, `.js` (components, styled-components, CSS-in-JS)
- `.css`, `.scss`, `.module.css` (stylesheets)

In a Claude Code host this corresponds to a `Stop` / post-edit checkpoint scoped
to the edited UI paths. Files that are not UI source do not trigger the gate.

## Action

Run the deterministic checker over the edited path:

```
/dsguard:check <edited-path> --system {{SYSTEM_NAME}}
```

which invokes the frozen, self-contained checker shipped with this plugin:

```bash
node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/checker.mjs <edited-path> \
  --config ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/checker-config.json
```

## Blocking rule

The checker's exit code is authoritative:

| Exit code | Result | Gate behaviour |
|-----------|--------|----------------|
| 0 | PASS — zero hard errors | Allow the workflow to complete |
| 1 | FAIL — one or more hard errors | **Block "done"** — surface each finding and require the violations be fixed |
| 2 | Configuration / I/O error | Surface the error; do not silently pass |

On exit code 1 the gate is **blocking**: the agent must not report the UI work as
complete until the checker passes (exit code 0). Re-run the check after fixing the
reported violations.
